{"id":33326,"date":"2019-08-31T20:20:41","date_gmt":"2019-08-31T16:20:41","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=33326"},"modified":"2025-07-03T14:06:19","modified_gmt":"2025-07-03T10:06:19","slug":"fasting-ashura-9th-muharram","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/08\/31\/fasting-ashura-9th-muharram\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on &#8216;Ashura: Fasting day of &#8216;Ashura with 9th of Muharram"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Al-Hakam ibn al-A\u2019raj reported: I went to Ibn Abbas, may Allah be pleased with him, and I said, \u201cTell me about fasting the day of &#8216;Ashura.\u201d Ibn Abbas said, \u201cWhen you see the crescent of the month of al-Muharram, count the days and wake up to fast on the ninth day.\u201d I said, \u201cIs this how the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, fasted it?\u201d Ibn Abbas said, \u201cYes.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1133<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Muslim<\/p>\n<p>Imam al-Nawawi commented, &#8220;Al-Shafi&#8217;i, his companions, Ahmad, Ishaq, and others said it is recommended to fast the ninth and tenth of al-Muharram together, as the Prophet fasted the tenth and intended to fast the ninth.&#8221;<\/p>\n<p>Source: Sharh\u0323 al-Nawawi\u0304 \u2018ala\u0301 S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 8\/12<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u062d\u064e\u0643\u064e\u0645\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0623\u064e\u0639\u0652\u0631\u064e\u062c\u0650 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0646\u0652\u062a\u064e\u0647\u064e\u064a\u0652\u062a\u064f \u0625\u0650\u0644\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0633\u064d \u0631\u0636\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0639\u0646\u0647\u0645\u0627 \u0641\u064e\u0642\u064f\u0644\u0652\u062a\u064f \u0644\u064e\u0647